A cyclist in his early 60s has died after a collision with a lorry in London, the sixth to die on the capital's roads in a fortnight.

Police were called to Camberwell Road in South London by London Ambulance Service at 12.07pm today, following reports of a collision involving a lorry and a cyclist.

A male cyclist, believed to be aged in his early 60s, suffered serious injuries and was pronounced dead at the scene half an hour later. Next of kin have been informed.

